From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mike Aizatsky <maizatskyi@cloudflare.com>
Date: Wed, 4 Mar 2026 13:19:20 -0800
Subject: Remove @libcxx dep from defs.bzl: not resolvable via http_archive

When V8 is loaded as an http_archive (not a bzlmod module), V8's own
MODULE.bazel is not processed by Bazel, so @libcxx cannot be created
via use_repo_rule. Remove the dependency since workerd provides its
own toolchain that includes libc++.

Author: Workerd Maintainers <workers-dev@cloudflare.com>

diff --git a/bazel/defs.bzl b/bazel/defs.bzl
index 0dbc6def7bb39d392c7178d3191972ebf4ec471d..609b9f07bfcb06a7451caf3f7db222bf740cd9b9 100644
--- a/bazel/defs.bzl
+++ b/bazel/defs.bzl
@@ -97,7 +97,7 @@ v8_config = rule(
 
 def _default_args():
     return struct(
-        deps = [":define_flags", "@libcxx//:libc++"],
+        deps = [":define_flags"],
         defines = select({
             "@v8//bazel/config:is_windows": [
                 "UNICODE",
